[35m[K./node_modules/redis/CHANGELOG.md[m[K[36m[K:[m[K1. [01;31m[Kredis[m[K.send_command commands have to be lower case from now on. This does only apply if you use `.send_command` directly instead of the convenient methods like `[01;31m[Kredis[m[K.command`.
[35m[K./node_modules/redis/CHANGELOG.md[m[K[36m[K:[m[K5. If [01;31m[Kredis[m[K can't connect to your [01;31m[Kredis[m[K server it'll give up after a certain point of failures (either max connection attempts or connection timeout exceeded). If that is the case it'll emit an CONNECTION_BROKEN error. You'll have to initiate a new client to try again afterwards.
[35m[K./node_modules/redis/CHANGELOG.md[m[K[36m[K:[m[K6. The offline queue is not flushed anymore on a reconnect. It'll stay until node_[01;31m[Kredis[m[K gives up trying to reach the server or until you close the connection.
[35m[K./node_modules/redis/CHANGELOG.md[m[K[36m[K:[m[K7. Before this release node_[01;31m[Kredis[m[K catched user errors and threw them async back. This is not the case anymore! No user behavior of what so ever will be tracked or catched.
[35m[K./node_modules/redis/CHANGELOG.md[m[K[36m[K:[m[K8. The keyspace of `[01;31m[Kredis[m[K.server_info` (db0...) is from now on an object instead of an string.

[35m[K./node_modules/redis/README.md[m[K[36m[K:[m[K**Note:** Using `'[01;31m[Kredis[m[Ks://...` for the protocol in a `[01;31m[Kredis[m[K_url` will enable a TLS socket connection. However, additional TLS options will need to be passed in `options`, if required.
[35m[K./node_modules/redis/README.md[m[K[36m[K:[m[K| url                        | null      | The URL of the Redis server. Format: `[[01;31m[Kredis[m[K[s]:]//[[user][:password@]][host][:port][/db-number][?db=db-number[&password=bar[&option=value]]]` (More info avaliable at [IANA](http://www.iana.org/assignments/uri-schemes/prov/[01;31m[Kredis[m[K)).                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |
[35m[K./node_modules/redis/README.md[m[K[36m[K:[m[K| string_numbers             | null      | Set to `true`, Node Redis will return Redis number values as Strings instead of javascript Numbers. Useful if you need to handle big numbers (above `Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER === 2^53`). Hi[01;31m[Kredis[m[K is incapable of this behavior, so setting this option to `true` will result in the built-in javascript parser being used no matter the value of the `parser` option.                                                                                                                                                                                                         |
[35m[K./node_modules/redis/README.md[m[K[36m[K:[m[K| no_ready_check             | false     | When a connection is established to the Redis server, the server might still be loading the database from disk. While loading, the server will not respond to any commands. To work around this, Node Redis has a "ready check" which sends the `INFO` command to the server. The response from the `INFO` command indicates whether the server is ready for more commands. When ready, `node_[01;31m[Kredis[m[K` emits a `ready` event. Setting `no_ready_check` to `true` will inhibit this check.                                                                                       |
[35m[K./node_modules/redis/README.md[m[K[36m[K:[m[K| rename_commands            | null      | Passing an object with renamed commands to use instead of the original functions. For example, if you renamed the command KEYS to "DO-NOT-USE" then the rename_commands object would be: `{ KEYS : "DO-NOT-USE" }` . See the [Redis security topics](http://[01;31m[Kredis[m[K.io/topics/security) for more info.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          |
[35m[K./node_modules/redis/README.md[m[K[36m[K:[m[K| connect_timeout            | 3600000   | In milliseconds. This should only be the timeout for connecting to [01;31m[Kredis[m[K, but for now it interferes with `retry_strategy` and stops it from reconnecting after this timeout.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
